On April 4, 2011, Obama announced his reelection campaign for 2012 in a video titled "It Begins with Us" that he posted on his website and filed election papers with the Federal Election Commission.[203][204][205] As the incumbent president, he ran virtually unopposed in the Democratic Party presidential primaries,[206] and on April 3, 2012, Obama had secured the 2778 convention delegates needed to win the Democratic nomination.[207]
